From: Raffaella del Prete <raffaellanz@icloud.com>
Sent: Tuesday, July 29, 2025 1:28 PM
To: Grant Metson <Grant.Metson@tower.co.nz>
Cc: Chris Cornwall <Chris.Cornwall@tower.co.nz>; Sasha Cotterill <Sasha.Cot=
terill@tower.co.nz>
Subject: Re: 23 Mays Road - progression of claims response. C90306048

Hi Grant, Thank you for your recent email and for the summary of our meetin=
g. I appreciate your efforts to move the claim forward. There are a few imp=
ortant matters I=E2=80=99d like to clarify to ensure the process remains sa=
fe, fair, and aligned with


Hi Grant,

Thank you for your recent email and for the summary of our meeting. I appre=
ciate your efforts to move the claim forward.

There are a few important matters I=E2=80=99d like to clarify to ensure the=
 process remains safe, fair, and aligned with Tower=E2=80=99s responsibilit=
ies under the policy.

First, regarding the items I took with me from the property =E2=80=94 inclu=
ding my electric vehicle (EV), laptops, tablets, and mobile phones =E2=80=
=94 these were all exposed to heat, smoke, and corrosive chemicals (includi=
ng nearby spa products that intensified the fire). I remain concerned about=
 internal damage, particularly to lithium batteries, and the potential for =
delayed failure or fire.

It is not appropriate or reasonable for Tower to shift the responsibility f=
or assessing or managing the risk of these items to me. Ensuring they are s=
afe for continued use is a critical safety issue =E2=80=94 not just a claim=
s matter. Tower must take responsibility for confirming whether these items=
 are safe, and whether they require restoration or replacement.

Second, I would appreciate clarification of Asset Restore=E2=80=99s scope. =
Is their role limited to cataloguing and removing contents, or will they al=
so be undertaking removal of fire- or smoke-damaged linings (such as jib an=
d other non-structural internal components)? This detail is important for u=
nderstanding when and how a proper structural assessment of the property wi=
ll take place.

Lastly, I would like to request a clear and updated plan for the progressio=
n of the house claim. Could you please provide:

  *   A current status update on the structural assessment and any scoping =
completed to date;
  *   A proposed timeline for the next phases: removal, scoping, approvals,=
 tendering, and repair;
  *   Confirmation of the parties responsible for each stage and how update=
s will be communicated.

I look forward to your response addressing the points above.

Kind regards,
Rafaella

________________________________

Let me know if you want to attach the policy wording or include any referen=
ces to specific clauses.


On 22 Jul 2025, at 12:19=E2=80=AFPM, Grant Metson <Grant.Metson@tower.co.nz=
<mailto:Grant.Metson@tower.co.nz>> wrote:

Good afternoon Rafaella,
I wanted to take the time to thank you very much for meeting with Chris, Da=
vid and myself at your place this afternoon. It was much appreciated.
I felt that the meeting was very productive and positive as we all discusse=
d the next steps and have agreed on the claim=E2=80=99s progression process=
 moving forward.
I would like to re-confirm the next steps we agreed to in writing, and shar=
e with all as below:


  1.  Asset Restore to attend site as soon as possible and complete the pro=
cess of assessing and cataloging the contents for the response of the conte=
nts claim. After assessment the contents which are categorised as a total l=
oss will be removed from site.
  2.  Asset Restore to strip out the property of any fire or smoke damaged =
linings or other non-structural items. This will enable a clear and clean s=
tructural assessment to be undertaken, from which we will produce a scope o=
f works for the repairs required.
  3.  Once we have a scope of works completed =E2=80=93 we will share this =
with you to approve before we submit to our repair panel for tendering.


Confirming that you have notified us of the access code to be 1106.
We will keep you updated on the above process and communicate with you as w=
e move through the above steps.

I have spoken with both our Motor and our Claims Team Leaders, and they hav=
e said that the items you have enquired about are very unlikely to be affec=
ted by the fire given their location with respect to the proximity of the f=
ire. I do understand that you would like to be 100% certain that the lithiu=
m batteries in these items have not been affected from the fire. The standa=
rd process in this situation is that you can undertake any testing of any o=
f your items which you wish to, to obtain test results or a report which yo=
ur insurer can consider for inclusion in your claims. If the test results p=
rove any damage or loss to these items from the fire =E2=80=93 then your in=
surer will consider them within your claim.

For contents items - please direct your enquiries to claims@tower.co.nz<mai=
lto:claims@tower.co.nz>
As you do not yet have a motor claim with Tower from this event =E2=80=93 y=
ou can also send any motor reports toclaims@tower.co.nz<mailto:claims@tower=
.co.nz> and they will respond accordingly.

Thank you again and I strongly encourage you to call me on the number below=
 with any concerns that you have with the process of the claim progression.
All the best,
Grant.


________________________________

