<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-line-height-alt:.75pt"><span style=3D"f=
ont-size:1.0pt;color:white">Hi Grant, Thank you for your recent email and f=
or the summary of our meeting. I appreciate your efforts to move the claim =
forward. There are a few important matters
 I=E2=80=99d like to clarify to ensure the process remains safe, fair, and =
aligned with<o:p></o:p></span></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-line-height-alt:.75pt"><span style=3D"f=
ont-size:1.0pt;color:white"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
</div>
<p>Hi Grant,<o:p></o:p></p>
<p>Thank you for your recent email and for the summary of our meeting. I ap=
preciate your efforts to move the claim forward.<o:p></o:p></p>
<p>There are a few important matters I=E2=80=99d like to clarify to ensure =
the process remains safe, fair, and aligned with Tower=E2=80=99s responsibi=
lities under the policy.<o:p></o:p></p>
<p>First, regarding the items I took with me from the property =E2=80=94 in=
cluding my electric vehicle (EV), laptops, tablets, and mobile phones =E2=
=80=94 these were all exposed to heat, smoke, and corrosive chemicals (incl=
uding nearby spa products that intensified the fire).
 I remain concerned about internal damage, particularly to lithium batterie=
s, and the potential for delayed failure or fire.<o:p></o:p></p>
<p>It is not appropriate or reasonable for Tower to shift the responsibilit=
y for assessing or managing the risk of these items to me. Ensuring they ar=
e safe for continued use is a critical safety issue =E2=80=94 not just a cl=
aims matter. Tower must take responsibility
 for confirming whether these items are safe, and whether they require rest=
oration or replacement.<o:p></o:p></p>
<p>Second, I would appreciate clarification of Asset Restore=E2=80=99s scop=
e. Is their role limited to cataloguing and removing contents, or will they=
 also be undertaking removal of fire- or smoke-damaged linings (such as jib=
 and other non-structural internal components)?
 This detail is important for understanding when and how a proper structura=
l assessment of the property will take place.<o:p></o:p></p>
<p>Lastly, I would like to request a clear and updated plan for the progres=
sion of the house claim. Could you please provide:<o:p></o:p></p>
<ul type=3D"disc">
<li style=3D"mso-list:l1 level1 lfo1">A current status update on the struct=
ural assessment and any scoping completed to date;<o:p></o:p></li><li style=
=3D"mso-list:l1 level1 lfo1">A proposed timeline for the next phases: remov=
al, scoping, approvals, tendering, and repair;<o:p></o:p></li><li style=3D"=
mso-list:l1 level1 lfo1">Confirmation of the parties responsible for each s=
tage and how updates will be communicated.<o:p></o:p></li></ul>
<p>I look forward to your response addressing the points above.<o:p></o:p><=
/p>
<p>Kind regards,<br>
Rafaella<o:p></o:p></p>
<div class=3D"MsoNormal" align=3D"center" style=3D"text-align:center">
<hr size=3D"2" width=3D"100%" align=3D"center">
</div>
<p>Let me know if you want to attach the policy wording or include any refe=
rences to specific clauses.<o:p></o:p></p>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><br>
<br>
<o:p></o:p></p>
<blockquote style=3D"margin-top:5.0pt;margin-bottom:5.0pt">
